threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, no section header

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This MIPS ELF binary is a botnet client designed to launch DDoS attacks. It uses direct syscalls instead of standard library imports for evasion. The malware daemonizes itself by forking and redirecting its standard streams to `/dev/null`. It then performs network scanning for vulnerable devices using SSDP discovery probes (M-SEARCH to 255.255.255.255:1900). It contains multiple functions for launching various network flood attacks, including sending a large, repetitive payload string (`/x38/xFJ/x93/xID/x9A/...`) to overwhelm targets.
